# Security Checks Rule

## Pre-publish checks
- Scan repository for token/key leakage patterns before commit/push.
- Scan for machine-specific absolute paths.
- Confirm source shebang portability.

## Sensitive patterns (minimum)
- `ghp_`
- `API_KEY`
- `TOKEN`
- `secret`
- `password`

## Path leakage patterns (minimum)
- `/Users/`
- `/opt/homebrew/Caskroom/`
- local private directories not required by product behavior

## Required outcome
- No credentials in tracked files.
- No accidental local-only paths in docs or source unless intentional and documented.
